Title : Ruth Rocha
Text : '''Ruth Machado Lousada Rocha''' (born March 2, 1931 in [[São Paulo]]), most known as '''Ruth Rocha''' is a Brazilian writer of children's books.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biografia-Ruth Rocha|url=http://www.tirodeletra.com.br/biografia/RuthRocha.htm|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> 
Together with [[Lygia Bojunga]], [[Ana Maria Machado]] and [[Eva Furnari]]  she is one of the leading exponents of the new wave of Brazilian children's literature.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ruth Rocha|url=http://escola.britannica.com.br/article/483520/Ruth-Rocha|work=Enciclopédia Escolar Britannica|publisher=Britannica Escola Online.|accessdate=29 April 2014|language=Portuguese}}</ref> Rocha graduated in Political Sociology at the [[University of São Paulo]] and postgraduated in Educational Orientation in the [[Pontifical Catholic University of São Paulo]]. She became a member of the Paulista Academy of Arts since October 25, 2007, occupying the chair 38.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ruth Rocha é imortal da Academia Paulista|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/impresso,ruth-rocha-e-imortal-da-academia-paulista,70965,0.htm|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=26 October 2007}}</ref>

==Work==
She debuted in the literary field in 1967, writing articles for several magazines on education, among them  [[Cláudia (magazine)|Cláudia]]. In 1976, she published her first book entitled Palavras Muitas Palavras .

Her current work has more than 130 published titles, 500 editions and translations to over 25 languages; also, it has sold about 17.5 million copies in Brazil and 2.5 million copies overseas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fada das letras|url=http://www.istoe.com.br/reportagens/22538_FADA+DAS+LETRAS|work=Revista Istoé|accessdate=29 April 2014|language=Portuguese|date=May 15, 2002}}</ref>  One of her best known works is Marcelo, Marmelo, Martelo, which has sold more than two million copies.

==Honors and Prizes==
In 1998 she was honored by former President [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]] with the [[Ordem do Mérito Cultural|Order of Cultural Merit]] from the Ministry of Culture of Brazil. In 2002 she was elected as a member of PEN CLUB - World Association of Writers in Rio de Janeiro. That same year, her book  Escrever e Criar received the [[Jabuti Prize]] of Literature.<ref>{{cite web|title=Prêmio 2001|url=http://premiojabuti.com.br/edicoes-anteriores/premio-2001/|work=Prêmio Jabuti|publisher=Câmara Brasileira do Livro|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>

